<main>
    <p>This page presents a variety of calculations for lati=C2=ADtude/long=
i=C2=ADtude points, with the formulas and
        code fragments for implementing them.</p>
    <p>All these formulas are for calculations on the basis of a spherical =
earth  (ignoring ellipsoidal
        effects) =E2=80=93 which is accurate enough<sup><a href=3D"https://=
www.movable-type.co.uk/scripts/latlong.html#ellipsoid" title=3D"see notes">=
*</a></sup> for
        most purposes=E2=80=A6 [In fact, the earth is very slightly ellipso=
idal; using a spherical model gives
        errors typically up to 0.3%<sup><a href=3D"http://gis.stackexchange=
.com/questions/25494#25580">1</a></sup>
        =E2=80=93 see notes for further details].</p>

