    <h3 id=3D"distance">Distance</h3>

    <p>This uses the =E2=80=98<b>haversine</b>=E2=80=99 formula to calculat=
e the great-circle distance between two
        points =E2=80=93 that is, the shortest distance over the earth=E2=
=80=99s surface =E2=80=93 giving an =E2=80=98as-the-crow-flies=E2=80=99
        distance between the  points (ignoring any hills they fly over, of =
course!).</p>
