        are no errors, otherwise they depend on distance, bearing, and lati=
tude, but are small enough
        for many purposes<sup title=3D"anyone care to quantify them?">*</su=
p> (and often trivial compared
        with the spherical approxima=C2=ADtion itself).</p>

    <p>Alternatively, the <i>polar coordinate flat-earth formula</i> can be=
