    <h4 id=3D"intermediate-point">Intermediate point</h4>

    <p>An intermediate point at any fraction along the great circle path be=
tween two points can also be
        calculated.<sup><a href=3D"http://www.edwilliams.org/avform.htm#Int=
ermediate" title=3D"from Ed William=E2=80=99s aviation formulary">1</a></su=
p></p>

    <table>
        <tbody><tr>
            <td class=3D"label">Formula:</td>
            <td class=3D"formula">a =3D sin((1=E2=88=92f)=E2=8B=85=CE=B4) /=
 sin =CE=B4</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">b =3D sin(f=E2=8B=85=CE=B4) / sin =CE=B4<=
/td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">x =3D a =E2=8B=85 cos =CF=86<sub>1</sub> =
=E2=8B=85 cos =CE=BB<sub>1</sub> + b =E2=8B=85 cos =CF=86<sub>2</sub> =E2=
=8B=85 cos =CE=BB<sub>2</sub></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">y =3D a =E2=8B=85 cos =CF=86<sub>1</sub> =
=E2=8B=85 sin =CE=BB<sub>1</sub> + b =E2=8B=85 cos =CF=86<sub>2</sub> =E2=
=8B=85 sin =CE=BB<sub>2</sub></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">z =3D a =E2=8B=85 sin =CF=86<sub>1</sub> =
+ b =E2=8B=85 sin =CF=86<sub>2</sub></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CF=86<sub>i</sub> =3D atan2(z, =E2=88=9A=
<span class=3D"radicand">x=C2=B2 + y=C2=B2)</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CE=BB<sub>i</sub> =3D atan2(y, x)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td class=3D"label align-right">where:</td>
            <td><i></i>f<i> is fraction along great circle route (f=3D0 is =
point 1, f=3D1 is point 2), </i>=CE=B4<i> is the angular
                distance </i>d/R<i> between the two points.</i></td>
        </tr>
    </tbody></table>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>

