    <h3 id=3D"intersection">Intersection of two paths given start points an=
d bearings</h3>

    <p>This is a rather more complex calculation than most others on this p=
age, but I've been asked for it a number of times.
        This comes from Ed William=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"http://www.edwillia=
ms.org/avform.htm#Intersection">aviation formulary</a>.
        See below for the JavaScript.</p>

    <form name=3D"intersect" id=3D"intersect">
        <fieldset><legend>Intersection of two great-circle paths</legend>
            <table class=3D"inputs">
                <tbody><tr>
                    <td>Point 1:</td>
                    <td>
                    <input name=3D"lat1" class=3D"lat1" type=3D"text" value=
=3D"51.8853 N" title=3D"Latitude 1">,
                    <input name=3D"lon1" class=3D"lon1" type=3D"text" value=
=3D"0.2545 E" title=3D"Longitude 1">
                    Brng 1:
                    <input name=3D"brng1" class=3D"brng1" type=3D"text" val=
ue=3D"108.55=C2=B0" title=3D"Bearing 1">
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Point 2:</td>
                    <td>
                    <input name=3D"lat2" class=3D"lat2" type=3D"text" value=
=3D"49.0034 N" title=3D"Latitude 2">,
                    <input name=3D"lon2" class=3D"lon2" type=3D"text" value=
=3D"2.5735 E" title=3D"Longitude 2">
                    Brng 2:
                    <input name=3D"brng1" class=3D"brng2" type=3D"text" val=
ue=3D"32.44=C2=B0" title=3D"Bearing 2">
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </tbody></table>
            <table class=3D"outputs">
                <tbody><tr>
                    <td>Intersection point:</td>
                    <td><output class=3D"result-point" title=3D"Intersectio=
n point">50=C2=B0=E2=80=AF54=E2=80=B2=E2=80=AF27=E2=80=B3=E2=80=AFN, 004=C2=
=B0=E2=80=AF30=E2=80=B2=E2=80=AF31=E2=80=B3=E2=80=AFE</output></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td colspan=3D"2"><p>&nbsp;</p></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody></table>
        </fieldset>
    </form>

    <table class=3D"clear-floats">
        <tbody><tr>
            <td class=3D"label">Formula:</td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CE=B4<sub>12</sub> =3D 2=E2=8B=85asin( =
=E2=88=9A<span class=3D"radicand">(sin=C2=B2(=CE=94=CF=86/2) + cos =CF=86<s=
ub>1</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CF=86<sub>2</sub> =E2=8B=85 sin=C2=B2(=CE=94=CE=
=BB/2))</span> )</td>
            <td class=3D"small grey align-right">angular dist. p1=E2=80=93p=
2</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CE=B8<sub>a</sub> =3D acos( ( sin =CF=86=
<sub>2</sub>  =E2=88=92 sin =CF=86<sub>1</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CE=B4<sub>12<=
/sub> ) / ( sin =CE=B4<sub>12</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CF=86<sub>1</sub> ) )<br=
>
                                =CE=B8<sub>b</sub> =3D acos( ( sin =CF=86<s=
ub>1</sub>  =E2=88=92 sin =CF=86<sub>2</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CE=B4<sub>12</s=
ub> ) / ( sin =CE=B4<sub>12</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CF=86<sub>2</sub> ) )</td>
            <td class=3D"small grey align-right">initial / final bearings<b=
r>between points 1 &amp; 2</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">if sin(=CE=BB<sub>2</sub>=E2=88=92=CE=BB<=
sub>1</sub>) &gt; 0<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=CE=B8<sub>12</sub> =3D =CE=B8<sub>=
a</sub><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=CE=B8<sub>21</sub> =3D 2=CF=80 =E2=
=88=92 =CE=B8<sub>b</sub><br>
                else<br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=CE=B8<sub>12</sub> =3D 2=CF=80 =E2=
=88=92 =CE=B8<sub>a</sub><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=CE=B8<sub>21</sub> =3D =CE=B8<sub>=
b</sub></td>
            <td class=3D"small grey align-right"></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CE=B1<sub>1</sub> =3D =CE=B8<sub>13</sub=
> =E2=88=92 =CE=B8<sub>12</sub><br>
                                =CE=B1<sub>2</sub> =3D =CE=B8<sub>21</sub> =
=E2=88=92 =CE=B8<sub>23</sub></td>
            <td class=3D"small grey align-right">angle p2=E2=80=93p1=E2=80=
=93p3<br>angle p1=E2=80=93p2=E2=80=93p3</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CE=B1<sub>3</sub> =3D acos( =E2=88=92cos=
 =CE=B1<sub>1</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CE=B1<sub>2</sub> + sin =CE=B1<sub>1</su=
b> =E2=8B=85 sin =CE=B1<sub>2</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CE=B4<sub>12</sub> )</td=
>
            <td class=3D"small grey align-right">angle p1=E2=80=93p2=E2=80=
=93p3</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CE=B4<sub>13</sub> =3D atan2( sin =CE=B4=
<sub>12</sub> =E2=8B=85 sin =CE=B1<sub>1</sub> =E2=8B=85 sin =CE=B1<sub>2</=
sub> , cos =CE=B1<sub>2</sub> + cos =CE=B1<sub>1</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CE=B1=
<sub>3</sub> )</td>
            <td class=3D"small grey align-right">angular dist. p1=E2=80=93p=
3</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CF=86<sub>3</sub> =3D asin( sin =CF=86<s=
ub>1</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CE=B4<sub>13</sub> + cos =CF=86<sub>1</sub> =E2=
=8B=85 sin =CE=B4<sub>13</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CE=B8<sub>13</sub> )</td>
            <td class=3D"small grey align-right">p3 lat</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CE=94=CE=BB<sub>13</sub> =3D atan2( sin =
=CE=B8<sub>13</sub> =E2=8B=85 sin =CE=B4<sub>13</sub> =E2=8B=85 cos =CF=86<=
sub>1</sub> , cos =CE=B4<sub>13</sub> =E2=88=92 sin =CF=86<sub>1</sub> =E2=
=8B=85 sin =CF=86<sub>3</sub> )</td>
            <td class=3D"small grey align-right">long p1=E2=80=93p3</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td class=3D"formula">=CE=BB<sub>3</sub> =3D =CE=BB<sub>1</sub>=
 + =CE=94=CE=BB<sub>13</sub></td>
            <td class=3D"small grey align-right">p3 long</td>
        </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class=3D"label align-right"><i>where</i></td>
        <td><p><i>=CF=86<sub>1</sub>, =CE=BB<sub>1</sub>, =CE=B8<sub>13</su=
b> : 1st start point &amp; (initial) bearing from 1st point towards interse=
ction point<br>
          =CF=86<sub>2</sub>, =CE=BB<sub>2</sub>, =CE=B8<sub>23</sub> : 2nd=
 start point &amp; (initial) bearing from 2nd point towards intersection po=
int<br>
          =CF=86<sub>3</sub>, =CE=BB<sub>3</sub> : intersection point</i></=
p>
            <p><i>% =3D (floating point) modulo<!--, | | =3D abs--></i></p>=
</td>
        <td></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class=3D"label align-right">note =E2=80=93</td>
        <td>if sin =CE=B1<sub>1</sub> =3D 0 and sin =CE=B1<sub>2</sub> =3D =
0: infinite solutions<br>
          if sin =CE=B1<sub>1</sub> =E2=8B=85 sin =CE=B1<sub>2</sub>  &lt; =
0: ambiguous solution<br>
          this formulation is not always well-conditioned for meridional or=
 equatorial lines</td>
        <td></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody></table>
<p>This is a lot simpler using vectors rather than spherical trigonometry:
    see <a href=3D"https://www.movable-type.co.uk/scripts/latlong-vectors.h=
tml#intersection">latlong-vectors.html</a>.</p>
