<h4 id=3D"rhumb-bearing">Bearing</h4>

<p>A rhumb line is a straight line on a Mercator projection, with an angle =
on the projec=C2=ADtion equal
    to the compass bearing.</p>

<table class=3D"width-full">
    <tbody><tr>
        <td class=3D"label">Formula: </td>
        <td class=3D"formula">=CE=94=CF=88 =3D ln( tan(=CF=80/4 + =CF=86<su=
b>2</sub>/2) / tan(=CF=80/4 + =CF=86<sub>1</sub>/2) )</td>
        <td></td>
    </tr>
